<TITLE> Barca friendly in Beijing more than just a game </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MADRID, May 26 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Barcelona will play a friendly against Chinese champions Beijing Guoan at the city's Bird's Nest stadium in August as they continue their efforts to tap into the lucrative Asian market. "This is more than just a game," Rafael Yuste, one of the club's vice presidents, told a news conference at the Nou Camp stadium in the Catalan capital on Tuesday. It was "definitive proof Barca is betting on the Asian market." The Spanish champions had already announced a friendly with an all-star South Korean league line-up in Seoul on Aug 4. They will play Guoan on Aug 8 at the iconic Bird's Nest arena built for the 2008 Olympics, the club said on their website (www.fcbarcelona.cat). It will be the fifth time Barcelona have played in China after games in Shanghai in 2004, Macao in 2005 and Beijing and Hong Kong in 
